    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-07T11:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-07T11:40:00-05:00" n="265"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d265">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1085.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Sullivan</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-07T12:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 7, 1914, 12 noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>If money for back salaries is not forthcoming at once Provisional Government will
                    go under. If you delay, our hold on the situation will be lost. Prompt relief
                    means keeping all our ground we have gained.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
